<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Document</title>
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
      integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/style.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>

    <div class="image-container" style="position: relative">
      <img
        decoding="async"
        sizes="100vw"
        srcset="
          https://framerusercontent.com/images/QUC1DPYvY9k6q9wes1rKIadFOFY.png?scale-down-to=512   512w,
          https://framerusercontent.com/images/QUC1DPYvY9k6q9wes1rKIadFOFY.png?scale-down-to=1024 1024w,
          https://framerusercontent.com/images/QUC1DPYvY9k6q9wes1rKIadFOFY.png?scale-down-to=2048 2048w,
          https://framerusercontent.com/images/QUC1DPYvY9k6q9wes1rKIadFOFY.png                    3320w
        "
        src="https://framerusercontent.com/images/QUC1DPYvY9k6q9wes1rKIadFOFY.png"
        alt="getting started with verse"
        style="
          display: block;
          width: 100%;
          height: 300px;
          border-radius: inherit;
          object-position: center center;
          object-fit: cover;
        "
      />

      <div
        class="text-content"
        style="
          position: absolute;
          top: 50%;
          left: 50%;
          transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
          text-align: center;
          color: white;
        "
      >
        <h1 style="font-size: 3rem">Getting Started</h1>
        <h5 style="font-size: 1.25rem">
          What you need to know to get started with Verse
        </h5>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faqDiv">
      <div class="faq1">
        <h3>What is Verse?</h3>
        <p>
          Verse is a blogging platform designed to let you create, view, and
          delete your blog posts with ease. It’s a place to share your thoughts,
          make<br />
          notes, and keep track of your insights. Whether you're a hobbyist or a
          professional, Verse provides a seamless and fun experience to express
          <br />your creativity.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq1">
        <h3>How can I use Verse?</h3>
        <p>
          Using Verse is simple! Just start writing. You can create new blog
          posts by adding titles and content, view them in a clean layout, and
          delete any outdated posts. The platform allows you to manage your
          content effortlessly—everything you need is at your fingertips!
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq1">
        <h3>What makes Verse different from other blogging platforms?</h3>
        <p>
          Verse offers an intuitive and minimalist interface that allows you to
          focus on your writing without distractions. Unlike other platforms,
          Verse emphasizes simplicity—giving you the freedom to create, manage,
          and delete posts easily while keeping your workflow smooth and
          efficient.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq1">
        <h3>Is Verse free to use?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes! Verse is completely free to use for anyone who wants to share
          their ideas, stories, or notes. There are no hidden fees or paid
          plans, so you can start blogging right away.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq1">
        <h3>Do I need to be a tech expert to use Verse?</h3>
        <p>
          Not at all! Verse is designed for everyone, whether you're a
          tech-savvy blogger or a beginner. The user-friendly interface makes it
          easy for anyone to start writing, managing, and sharing their content
          with just a few clicks.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq1">
        <h3>Can I view posts made by other users?</h3>
        <p>
          At the moment, Verse is focused on individual blogging, so your posts
          are private. However, in future updates, we plan to add features to
          explore other users' posts and connect with the blogging community!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>
    <script
      src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
      integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    ></script>
  </body>
</html>
